<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/169</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Johnson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-20T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1917—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram June 15, noon. Your action therein set forth is approved.
                            For your guidance you are confidentially informed that this Government
                            will not look with approval upon any revolution in the personal interest
                            of Gonzáles or Quesada, and they have been so advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>